= mxcli: AI-Powered Development for Mendix
<mxcli-ai-powered-development-for-mendix>
#strong[Accelerate Mendix Development with Natural Language and Code Generation]

== Executive Summary
<executive-summary>
#strong[mxcli] is a command-line interface that brings AI-powered development to the Mendix platform. By providing a SQL-like language called #strong[MDL (Mendix Definition Language)];, mxcli enables developers and AI assistants to read, understand, and modify Mendix projects programmatically.

=== Key Benefits
<key-benefits>
- #strong[10x Faster Development];: Generate domain models, microflows, and pages using natural language
- #strong[Consistent Standards];: Define organizational best practices as MDL templates
- #strong[AI-Native Integration];: Purpose-built for GenAI code assistants like Claude Code
- #strong[Full Project Understanding];: Agentic search capabilities for intelligent code navigation
- #strong[Token-Efficient];: MDL uses 5-10x fewer tokens than JSON model representations, reducing API costs
- #strong[Better Code Reviews];: Higher information density makes diffs easier to read and review

#horizontalrule

== How It Works
<how-it-works>
```
┌─────────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐
│   Developer     │     │    mxcli     │     │ Mendix Project  │
│   or AI Agent   │────▶│  (MDL REPL)  │────▶│   (.mpr file)   │
│                 │ MDL │              │     │                 │
│ "Create a       │     │ Parses MDL   │     │ Creates actual  │
│  Customer       │     │ Validates    │     │ entities,       │
│  entity..."     │     │ Executes     │     │ microflows,     │
└─────────────────┘     └──────────────┘     │ pages, etc.     │
                                             └─────────────────┘
```

=== The MDL Advantage
<the-mdl-advantage>
MDL is a #strong[text-based, SQL-like language] that describes Mendix model elements. Compared to the visual Studio Pro interface and JSON model representations, MDL offers:

- #strong[Generated by AI];: LLMs produce syntactically correct MDL with high accuracy
- #strong[Human-Readable Diffs];: Text-based format is easier to review than binary or JSON changes
- #strong[High Information Density];: Scan complete microflow logic at a glance, without clicking through activities
- #strong[Token Efficient];: 5-10x fewer tokens than JSON representations, allowing more application context in LLM prompts
- #strong[Concise Skill Documents];: Smaller, more precise AI instruction files lead to better generation quality
- #strong[Templated for Reuse];: Standard patterns become simple copy-paste snippets

=== Why Token Efficiency Matters
<why-token-efficiency-matters>
When working with GenAI APIs, #strong[context window size is a critical constraint];. MDL's compact syntax provides significant advantages over JSON model representations:

#figure(
  align(center)[#table(
    columns: 2,
    align: (auto,auto,),
    table.header([Representation], [Tokens for a 10-entity module],),
    table.hline(),
    [JSON (raw model)], [\~15,000-25,000 tokens],
    [MDL], [\~2,000-4,000 tokens],
    [#strong[Savings];], [#strong[5-10x fewer tokens];],
  )]
  , kind: table
  )

#strong[Benefits of token efficiency:]

+ #strong[Lower API costs];: Fewer tokens = lower costs per request
+ #strong[More context available];: Fit more of your application in a single prompt
+ #strong[Better AI understanding];: Less noise, more signal in the context
+ #strong[Faster responses];: Smaller payloads process more quickly
+ #strong[Larger scope operations];: Modify multiple entities, microflows, and pages in one request

#strong[Example comparison:]

```json
// JSON representation (~180 tokens)
{
  "entity": {
    "name": "Customer",
    "documentation": "Customer master data",
    "attributes": [
      {"name": "Name", "type": {"type": "String", "length": 200}},
      {"name": "Email", "type": {"type": "String", "length": 200}}
    ]
  }
}
```

```sql
-- MDL representation (~35 tokens)
/** Customer master data */
CREATE PERSISTENT ENTITY Sales.Customer (
    Name: String(200),
    Email: String(200)
);
```

This efficiency extends to skill documents---the AI instruction files that guide generation. Concise MDL examples in skills mean: - More patterns fit in the skill document - AI has clearer examples to follow - Generated output is more accurate and consistent

