=== Workflow Integration
<workflow-integration>
```sql
/** Define business workflows */
CREATE WORKFLOW Sales.OrderApproval
FOR Sales.Order
BEGIN
    STATE Draft
        ON Submit GOTO PendingApproval
            WHEN TotalAmount > 0;

    STATE PendingApproval
        ASSIGN TO Role 'Sales.Manager'
        ON Approve GOTO Approved
        ON Reject GOTO Rejected
            REQUIRE Comment;

    STATE Approved
        ON Ship GOTO Shipped
        TRIGGER MICROFLOW Sales.NotifyCustomer;

    STATE Shipped
        ON Deliver GOTO Completed;

    STATE Completed
        FINAL;

    STATE Rejected
        ON Revise GOTO Draft
        FINAL;
END;
```

=== VS Code Extension and Language Server
<vs-code-extension-and-language-server>
The `vscode-mdl` extension provides comprehensive MDL language support in VS Code, Cursor, and other compatible editors. The extension is #strong[auto-installed] when you run `mxcli init`.

==== Installation
<installation>
#strong[Automatic (Recommended):]

```bash
# Initialize project - auto-installs extension if `code` CLI is available
mxcli init /path/to/mendix-project
```

#strong[Manual Installation:]

```bash
# Build extension package
make vscode-ext           # Builds .vsix package

# Install into VS Code
make vscode-install       # Builds and installs

# Or install from .vsix manually
code --install-extension vscode-mdl/vscode-mdl-*.vsix
```

If `code` CLI isn't available during `mxcli init`, the extension is extracted to `.claude/vscode-mdl.vsix` for manual installation.

==== Features
<features>
#strong[Syntax and Validation:] - #strong[Syntax Highlighting] - Color-coded MDL keywords, types, strings, comments (TextMate grammar) - #strong[Parse Diagnostics] - Real-time error detection as you type (no project required) - #strong[Semantic Diagnostics] - Reference validation on save (checks entity/microflow/page references against `.mpr`) - #strong[Document Symbols] - Outline view listing all CREATE/ALTER/DROP statements - #strong[Folding Ranges] - Collapsible BEGIN/END, IF/END IF, LOOP/END LOOP, braces, parentheses

#strong[Navigation:] - #strong[Hover] - Shows MDL definition for `Module.Entity` qualified names (via `mxcli describe`) - #strong[Go to Definition] - Ctrl+click/Cmd+click on qualified names opens virtual MDL document - #strong[Code Completion] - Context-aware keyword suggestions (e.g., after `CREATE`, `SHOW`)

#strong[Execution:] - #strong[Context Menu Commands:] - #strong[Run File] - Execute entire MDL file against project - #strong[Run Selection] - Execute selected MDL statements - #strong[Check File] - Validate syntax and references without execution

#strong[Example - Right-click context menu:]

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│  your-script.mdl                    │
│  ┌──────────────────────────────────│
│  │ CREATE PERSISTENT ENTITY ...     │
│  │                                  │
│  │ [Right-click menu]               │
│  │ ├─ Run File                      │
│  │ ├─ Run Selection                 │
│  │ ├─ Check File                    │
│  │ └─ Check File (with references)  │
└──┴──────────────────────────────────┘
```

==== Configuration
<configuration>
#strong[VS Code Settings] (`settings.json`):

```json
{
  // Path to mxcli binary (default: "mxcli" from PATH)
  "mdl.mxcliPath": "/path/to/mxcli",

  // Path to .mpr file (auto-discovered if empty)
  "mdl.mprPath": "/path/to/project.mpr"
}
```

#strong[Project Auto-Discovery:] When `mdl.mprPath` is not set, the extension searches the workspace for `.mpr` files. If exactly one is found, it's used automatically.

#strong[Project-Aware Features:] Features requiring project access (hover, definition, semantic diagnostics) gracefully degrade when no `.mpr` is configured. Core features (syntax highlighting, parse diagnostics, completion, symbols, folding) work without a project.

==== Language Server Protocol (LSP)
<language-server-protocol-lsp>
The extension communicates with `mxcli lsp --stdio` as the language server. This architecture enables: - Use with any LSP-compatible editor (not just VS Code) - Consistent behavior across editors - Single implementation for all MDL tooling

#strong[LSP Server Capabilities:]

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  VS Code / Cursor / Other LSP-Compatible Editors           │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│  your-script.mdl                                            │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐│
│  │ CREATE PERSISTENT ENTITY Sales.█                       ││
│  │                          ┌──────────────────┐          ││
│  │                          │ Customer         │          ││
│  │                          │ Order            │          ││
│  │                          │ Product          │          ││
│  │                          │ OrderLine        │          ││
│  │                          └──────────────────┘          ││
│  │                          ▲ Autocomplete suggestions    ││
│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘│
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#strong[Using LSP with Other Editors:]

```bash
# Start language server manually (reads from stdin, writes to stdout)
mxcli lsp --stdio

# Configure your editor to spawn this command when opening .mdl files
```

