== CLI Commands Reference
<cli-commands-reference>
mxcli provides a rich set of commands for project analysis, code search, and development workflows.

=== Project Initialization
<project-initialization>
```bash
# Initialize with Claude Code (default)
mxcli init /path/to/mendix-project

# Initialize for a specific AI tool
mxcli init --tool cursor /path/to/mendix-project

# Initialize for multiple tools
mxcli init --tool claude --tool cursor --tool continue

# Initialize for all supported tools
mxcli init --all-tools

# List supported tools
mxcli init --list-tools

# What it creates (universal):
# - .ai-context/skills/ - MDL pattern guides (shared by all tools)
# - AGENTS.md - Universal AI assistant guide
#
# What it creates (Claude Code specific):
# - .claude/settings.json - Claude Code permissions
# - .claude/commands/ - Slash commands
# - .claude/lint-rules/ - Starlark lint rules
# - CLAUDE.md - Project instructions
# - VS Code MDL extension (auto-installed if `code` CLI available)
```

=== Script Execution
<script-execution>
```bash
# Execute an MDL script file
mxcli exec script.mdl -p app.mpr

# Execute commands directly
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "SHOW ENTITIES"
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "SHOW MODULES"

# Check syntax without executing (validation only)
mxcli check script.mdl

# Check syntax with reference validation (requires project)
mxcli check script.mdl -p app.mpr --references
```

=== Code Search and Navigation
<code-search-and-navigation>
These commands require a catalog refresh first (`REFRESH CATALOG FULL` or `mxcli -p app.mpr -c "REFRESH CATALOG FULL"`):

```bash
# Find what calls a microflow (callers)
mxcli callers -p app.mpr Module.MyMicroflow
mxcli callers -p app.mpr Module.MyMicroflow --transitive

# Find what a microflow calls (callees)
mxcli callees -p app.mpr Module.MyMicroflow

# Find all references to an element
mxcli refs -p app.mpr Module.Customer

# Analyze impact of changing an element
mxcli impact -p app.mpr Module.Customer

# Assemble context for LLM consumption
mxcli context -p app.mpr Module.MyMicroflow --depth 3

# Full-text search across strings and source
mxcli search -p app.mpr "validation"
mxcli search -p app.mpr "validation" -q --format names
mxcli search -p app.mpr "validation" -q --format json
```

#strong[Search Output Formats:] - `names` (default) - `type<TAB>name` per line, suitable for piping - `json` - JSON array of results - `-q` flag - Quiet mode (no headers/formatting)

#strong[Example: Pipe search results to describe:]

```bash
mxcli search -p app.mpr "error" -q --format names | head -1 | awk '{print $2}' | \
  xargs mxcli describe -p app.mpr microflow
```

=== Project Introspection
<project-introspection>
```bash
# Describe a specific element (outputs MDL source)
mxcli describe -p app.mpr entity Module.EntityName
mxcli describe -p app.mpr microflow Module.MicroflowName
mxcli describe -p app.mpr page Module.PageName
mxcli describe -p app.mpr snippet Module.SnippetName

# Show project elements
mxcli show -p app.mpr modules
mxcli show -p app.mpr entities --module MyModule
mxcli show -p app.mpr microflows --module MyModule
mxcli show -p app.mpr pages --module MyModule

# Output project structure as JSON
mxcli project-tree -p app.mpr
```

=== Linting
<linting>
```bash
# Lint a project for issues
mxcli lint -p app.mpr

# With colored output
mxcli lint -p app.mpr --color

# JSON output for CI integration
mxcli lint -p app.mpr --format json

# SARIF output for GitHub integration
mxcli lint -p app.mpr --format sarif > results.sarif

# List available rules
mxcli lint -p app.mpr --list-rules

# Exclude modules from linting
mxcli lint -p app.mpr --exclude System --exclude Administration
```

#strong[Built-in Lint Rules:] - #strong[MDL001 (NamingConvention)] - PascalCase for entities, microflows, pages, enumerations - #strong[MDL002 (EmptyMicroflow)] - No microflows with zero activities - #strong[MDL003 (DomainModelSize)] - Max 15 persistent entities per domain model - #strong[MDL004 (ValidationFeedback)] - Validation feedback must have non-empty message

=== Diff and Comparison
<diff-and-comparison>
```bash
# Compare MDL script against project state (dry run preview)
mxcli diff -p app.mpr changes.mdl

# Compare local changes against git (MPR v2 only)
mxcli diff-local -p app.mpr --ref HEAD
mxcli diff-local -p app.mpr --ref HEAD~1
```

=== Styling Commands
<styling-commands>
```bash
# Discover available design properties from theme
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "SHOW DESIGN PROPERTIES"
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "SHOW DESIGN PROPERTIES FOR CONTAINER"

# Inspect styling on existing pages/snippets
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "DESCRIBE STYLING ON PAGE MyModule.CustomerEdit"
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "DESCRIBE STYLING ON PAGE MyModule.CustomerEdit WIDGET btnSave"

# Modify styling on existing pages/snippets
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "ALTER STYLING ON PAGE MyModule.CustomerEdit WIDGET btnSave SET Class 'btn-lg'"
mxcli -p app.mpr -c "ALTER STYLING ON SNIPPET MyModule.NavMenu WIDGET ctn1 SET 'Spacing top' 'Large'"
```

=== Widget Discovery (EXPERIMENTAL)
<widget-discovery-experimental>
#strong[Warning];: These commands are proof-of-concept. Always use `DRY RUN` first and backup your project.

```bash
# Discover widgets in project (requires REFRESH CATALOG FULL)
./bin/mxcli -p app.mpr -c "SHOW WIDGETS"
./bin/mxcli -p app.mpr -c "SHOW WIDGETS IN MyModule"
./bin/mxcli -p app.mpr -c "SHOW WIDGETS WHERE WidgetType LIKE '%combobox%'"

# Preview changes (dry run)
./bin/mxcli -p app.mpr -c "UPDATE WIDGETS SET 'showLabel' = false WHERE WidgetType LIKE '%combobox%' DRY RUN"

# Apply changes
./bin/mxcli -p app.mpr -c "UPDATE WIDGETS SET 'showLabel' = false WHERE WidgetType LIKE '%combobox%' IN MyModule"
```

