== Getting Started
<getting-started>
=== 1. Initialize Your Project
<initialize-your-project>
```bash
# Navigate to your Mendix project folder
cd /path/to/your-mendix-project

# Initialize mxcli (creates .ai-context/, CLAUDE.md, etc.)
./mxcli init
```

=== 2. Connect and Explore
<connect-and-explore>
```bash
# Start the interactive REPL
./mxcli

# Connect to your project
mendix> CONNECT LOCAL 'MyProject.mpr';

# Explore the model
mendix> SHOW MODULES;
mendix> SHOW ENTITIES IN MyFirstModule;
mendix> DESCRIBE ENTITY MyFirstModule.Customer;
```

=== 3. Use with Claude Code
<use-with-claude-code>
Open your project in VS Code with Claude Code extension. The AI can now:

- Answer questions about your model
- Generate new entities, microflows, and pages
- Refactor existing elements
- Apply your organization's templates

=== 4. Execute MDL Scripts
<execute-mdl-scripts>
```bash
# Execute a script file
./mxcli -d "EXECUTE SCRIPT 'mdlsource/setup-sales-module.mdl'"

# Or run individual commands
./mxcli -d "SHOW MODULES"
./mxcli -d "CREATE MODULE Sales"
```

